<dl id="n40099c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40099c">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40099c"> 99(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> cur in the / potters&apos; kiln</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">O dear my son, thou hast been the cur who, when suffering cold entereth the potter&apos;s house to warm himself at the kiln, and when warmed barketh at the folk &hellip; <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RFBS" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#RFBS"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night with Notes Anthropological and Explanatory</cite></a> (n.d.) xvi.28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
